instance: A dull head between windy spaces.
A beautiful, pedantic sun in a satin vest.
A silence permeates the story and a softness in the narrator's eyes.
And the storm must be painful

But through the thin pale water
The harmless feet still shine

Every streetlight I pass
It sounds like a fatalistic drum
Hope is that feathery thing that settles in the soul and sings the melody without the words and never stops at all.
I do not deteriorate beauty by being mute
I have heard it in the coldest land
The heart of the ocean is too soft, too blue.

The reminiscence comes
Of dried geraniums without sun
The yellow fog that brushes your back against the windows
The yellow smoke that rubs its snout against the glass
Under a windy knob.
Where the worried bodies of drowned men float in the green silence
a crow that flies in the sweetest air of heaven
A woman's face hand painted by nature.
As sweet season rains fall to the ground
Hiding your bravery in its rotten smoke
silenced the shrunken seas
kissing the green meadows with a golden face
the beauty of my sweet love
Sometimes too hot the eye of the sky shines
that sweet smell
the bottoms of silent seas.
the sessions of sweet silent thinking
the wide world and all its faded sweets
its substance still lives sweet
listening with your eyes belongs to the fine ingenuity of love
your sweet resemblance to some other day
